Kim Jong Il Enjoys Art Performance Given by Russian State Chorus 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong I enjoyed an art performance given by the Russian State Academic People's Chorus Named after M. E. Pyatnichki on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greeted at a theater by Aleksandra Permyakova, head of the chorus, and Valery Sukhinin, Russian ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He warmly welcomed the visit of the chorus to the DPRK and thanked for the joy and encouragement given by its artistes to the people of the DPRK through a series of its enthusiastic performances before having a cordial talk with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chorus, which has a 97 year-long history and tradition, put on the stage colorful numbers newly created by it including dance "At Evening and Middle of Night", choruses "Russia, the Motherland", "May My Voice Reverberate" and "Along the Mother River Volga", chorus and dance "To Our Katsya", female chorus and instrumental music "At the Side of the River Don", male vocal solo "White Birches", glee "Something Urgent Has Happened," dance "Jokers of Belgorod Region", instrumental music "Polka of Russia", chorus and dance "Russian Fun." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance made a truthful artistic representation of patriotism and optimistic life of the Russian people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He congratulated the artistes on their successful performance and extended greetings to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK Kim Ki Nam, First Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kang Sok Ju, Generals of the Korean People's Army Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su, KPA servicepersons and creators and artistes of the army and society.

Talks between DPRK and Vietnamese Delegations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- Talks were held between the delegations of the Korea-Vietnam Friendship Parliamentary Group and the Vietnam-Korea Friendship Parliamentary Group at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were members of the Korea-Vietnam Friendship Parliamentary Group led by its Chairman Kim Wan Su and from the opposite side members of the Vietnam-Korea Friendship Parliamentary Group led by its Chairman Ksor Phuoc who is also chairman of the National Council of the Vietnamese National Assembly and Vietnamese Ambassador Le Van Cu to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on further developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two parliaments and a series of matters of mutual concern.

Delegation of the Ministry of People's Security Leaves 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Ministry of People's Security led by its Minister Ju Sang Song left here today to visit Vietnam and Laos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arriving here by air on the same day was a delegation of the Fukuoka Prefectural Japan-DPRK Friendship Association headed by its Representative Mamoru Kitahara.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with gifts by the delegation of the Association for Promotion of Development of Chinese Culture and the adviser to the president of Far Eastern National University of Technology of Russia participating in the 6th Pyongyang International Science and Technology Book Fair. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Secretary General Xin Qi who is the head of the Chinese delegation and Adviser to the president of the Russian University Genazi Turmov separately handed the gifts to an official concerned.

Participants of Pyongyang International Book Fair Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The Organizing Committee of the 6th Pyongyang International Science and Technology Book Fair and the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries hosted a reception at the People's Palace of Culture on Monday in honor of the participants in the fair. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were delegations of different countries, international organizations and overseas compatriots to the fair and representatives and officials of foreign embassies here and officials of missions of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairman of the fair organizing committee, Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the KCCRFC, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

11th National Taekwon-Do Championship for Jongilbong Cup Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The 11th national Taekwon-Do championship for Jongilbong Cup was opened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It brought together at least 800 players selected from more than 10 units including Taekwon-Do players' groups, Taekwon-Do schools and schoolchildren's palaces. They will compete in Taekwon-Do, go and Korean wrestling events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening ceremony was held at the Taekwon-Do Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hwang Pong Yong, chairman of the Korean Taekwon-Do Committee, made an opening speech. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was followed by an exhibition presentation by players of the group of the Korean Taekwon-Do Committee.

Health Promotion Products Developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The Korea Kongang Joint Venture Co. under the Ministry of Public Health has recently developed products good for health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Eisenokinase capsule (Lumbrokinase) is a thrombolytic agent of new generation, which is made by refining thrombolytic enzyme extracted from Eisenia foetida with cutting-edge technology. The earthworm has long been used as medicines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The efficacy of the newly developed capsule is scores of times that of the existing thrombolytic agents. It shows an ideal efficacy in the prevention and treatment of stenocardia, headache, peripheral blood circulation disorder and cerebral thrombosis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Its treatment efficacy is above 90 percents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The company has also developed a new kind of computer screen filter, the filtering efficacy of which is considerably larger than that of the existing ones.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The filter shuts out ultraviolet rays and absorbs positive ions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It has been tested on thousands of persons who work at computer for six hours a day. The result shows that they do not complain of any headache, ache in joints and eyes and fatigue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The newly-made 20-mW general semiconductor laser curative machine is very popular as it is used for the treatment of various diseases including hemorrhoids, prostate gland disorders and women's diseases and for needle treatment by laser rays.

Adherence to Principle of Self-Reliance Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- Self-reliance is the life and soul of the Korean people, and it is their unshakable will that one is sure to emerge a victor if one adheres to the principle of self-reliance to the last and one is destined to go to ruin if one abandons it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a joint signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely thanks to self-reliance that the Korean people who were oppressed, undergoing bitter sorrow as a stateless nation in the past, are now leading a dignified and worthwhile life as masters of their destinies, the article notes, and go on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance is the only way out for us and we should follow this way under any circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The drive to open up the gate to a great prosperous powerful nation is a worthwhile march to make everything flourish and people lead an abundant life through leaping advances made in all fields including economy, culture, science and technology. Supremacy, profit and "high rate" of economic growth sought by others do not have anything common with the Korean people's efforts to achieve the above-said goal. The country pervaded with the spirit of self-reliance is the true picture of the great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will never step back even an inch from the path of self-reliance chosen by themselves but scale the high eminence of the above-said nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance is the signpost for their own life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should give the fullest play to the inexhaustible energies, wisdom and enthusiasm and thus glorify this year, the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK, as a year of self-reliance under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, a great pioneer of self-reliance.

U.S. Chiefly to Blame for Nuclear Threat and Arms Race
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- U.S. Secretary of Defense Gates, addressing officers of U.S. forces in an air force base in Virginia State some days ago, cried out for bolstering the nuclear forces in order to "deter potential enemies' provocations," mentioning Russia, Iran and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This comes under fire by a signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun today. The U.S. loud-mouthed "peace" and "disarmament" are, in essence, a slogan for beefing up the nuclear forces and stepping up arms race, the commentary notes, citing facts that the U.S. is becoming evermore frantic in its moves to bolster its armed forces including nuclear weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' policy for bolstering their nuclear forces and stepping up the arms race is creating the danger of fresh global arms race and nuclear stand-off and rendering the situation tenser. This fact clearly proves that the U.S. is a disturber of peace, not a "peace champion," and the mastermind of nuclear threat and proliferation and arms race. With nothing can the U.S. justify its policy of arms race and moves for a war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces will not be able to escape international isolation and destruction, should they rush headlong into arms race and a war of aggression quite contrary to the trend of the present times towards disarmament and peace and wishes of humankind, warns the commentary.

Pro-U.S. Conservative Forces in S. Korea Accused of Inciting Confrontation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The "Reservists' Association", an ultra-rightist conservative organization in south Korea, recently published and distributed copies of anti-communist comic book "Proper Understanding of June 25 War" not only to primary, middle and high schools but to kindergartens in Seoul, stirring up great public furor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday terms the comic book an extremely reactionary one as it described man-killer MacArthur as a "benefactor" and "hero" though he inflicted immeasurable misfortune and disasters upon the Korean nation during the past Korean war and claimed that any call for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea is little short of "being taken in by the north's strategy".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more intolerable is the fact that the author of the book described the April 3 People's Uprising on Jeju Island and the Ryosu Resistance, the just national salvation resistances of the south Korean people, as "atrocities" by linking them with the north and malignantly slandered the inter-Korean cooperation undertakings conducted in the June 15 era of reunification, groundlessly charging that they "helped maintain the system in the north", the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should not be overlooked that such anti-communist books grossly distorting the history and malignantly slandering the north are openly distributed in south Korea. This is a product of the sinister plots of the pro-U.S. conservative forces to quell the spirit of independence against the U.S. growing stronger among the people, youth and students of south Korea and zealously incite the hostility toward the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said organization's publication and distribution of such undesirable comic books agitating sycophancy toward the U.S. and confrontation with fellow countrymen are nothing but an unpardonable provocation against the DPRK and, at the same time, an act of treachery as it is aimed at blocking the national reconciliation and unity and agitating inter-Korean confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distribution of such large number of copies of disturbing books to various educational institutions including even kindergartens was possible only with the patronage, connivance and back-stage manipulation of the puppet authorities.

Unremitting Movement for Korea's Reunification Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- Vigorous struggles are now going on in south Korea to condemn the Lee Myung Bak regime's treacherous and anti-national moves. They are a revelation of the just and patriotic will to put an end to the foreign forces' domination and the sycophantic traitors' treacherous rule, restore the dignity and sovereignty of the nation and achieve the national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National reunification, the cherished desire of the Korean nation, can be achieved only through struggle against the moves of the separatist forces at home and abroad, it says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After taking office in south Korea, the Lee Myung Bak group is laying a very grave stumbling block to the development of inter-Korean relations and the progress of the national reunification movement by being hell-bent on the pro-U.S. sycophantic and anti-reunification moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result, democracy and human rights are ruthlessly trampled underfoot in south Korea and the north-south relationship turned back to that in the past era of confrontation and the cause of national reunification is undergoing serious ups and downs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If such moves of the Lee group seeking to check the advance of the era of independent reunification while zealously following the outsiders' policy for division and aggression are not frustrated, all the achievements made after the adoption of the June 15 joint declaration would be spoiled and it would be impossible to achieve reconciliation and unity between the north and the south, peace of the Korean Peninsula and the national reunification and co-prosperity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The anti-"government" struggle vigorously waged by the south Korean people at present is a resistance of justice to achieve the independent development and democracy of society and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No change can be made as long as the Lee group remains in office, and there is nothing to expect from it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people should never be taken in deceptive trick of traitor Lee Myung Bak nor put down the candlelight of anger till their demands are met.

S. Koreans Called upon to Turn out in Candlelight Actions
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Markets to American Beef issued a statement titled "People's resistance will go on as long as the regime refuses to conduct renegotiations by telling lies and making excuses" on June 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the "special press conference" called by Lee Myung Bak that day, the statement expressed irrepressible disappointment and indignation at the traitor as he hoodwinked the people again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The council strongly condemns the "special press conference" called by Lee at which he flatly refused to satisfy the people's desire reflected in the one million candlelight struggle, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The council will stage the second grand all-people candlelight march for the total renegotiations on beef import and the judgment of the Lee Myung Bak "government" during the "48 hour-long emergency people's action" and support and solidarize with people in their actions against such wrong policies of the "government" as the moves to put public media under its control and "campus autonomy".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called upon the people to turn out in the candlelight struggle to judge the unpopular policies of the "government" which gives priority to seeking profits.

Cancel of "Great Canal Project" Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The People's Action for Nullification of Canal Project in south Korea called a press conference in Seoul on June 20 to demand that Lee Myung Bak make clear his stand on the retraction of the "great canal project." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization referred to the fact that Lee told at the "special press conference" on June 19 that the "project" would not be carried forward if the people stand against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such equivocal stand, manifested by him on the "project" with the above-said conditional watchword at the time when over 80 percent of the population has already protested it, casts doubt about his true intention, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It held that if what he said is true, he should clearly declare the nullification of the "project" and take immediate follow-up steps for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee should never forget the meaning of the candlelight actions staged across south Korea, the organization said, warning that the people will not allow any attempt to ignore their supreme call for the abandonment of the "project." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stated that it would scrutinize follow-up steps to be taken by the Lee "government" and more strongly counter, together with the people, any attempts to upset the recent decision.

48 Hour-long Emergency People's Action Staged throughout S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- A "48 hour-long emergency people's action" demanding total renegotiations on the import of American beef was staged across south Korea from June 20 to 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 46th candlelight rally on the theme of "Candlelight rally is sure to triumph. Conduct total renegotiations" took place in the plaza of the City Office in Seoul on June 22. It was attended by at least 10,000 citizens from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally said that more than 130,000 citizens turned out in various parts of Seoul including the plaza of the City Office, the plaza of Chonggye, the University Street and Youido while the "48 hour-long emergency people's action" was under way from the day after the hypocritical "special press conference" was held by traitor Lee Myung Bak, demonstrating once again the will of the people to get the renegotiations conducted on the import of the American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They dismissed the "special press conference" at which Lee Myung Bak uttered "apology" and the like a sheer charade to deceive people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Declaring that the group of traitors will set in motion paid trumpeters for misleading the public opinion from the moment candlelight actions are ceased, they called for not stopping the struggle but holding higher candlelight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded the immediate firing of the chief of the Police Agency who rushed police force to crack down with shields and jackboots upon those citizens participating in the candlelight actions against the import of American beef and the chief of the Headquarters of the Trade Negotiations who conducted humiliating additional negotiations with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally its participants marched through main thoroughfares of the city.

Kim Jong Il's Party Leadership Feats Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- Figures of Bangladesh, Egypt and Syria issued statements on the occasion of the 44th anniversary of the start of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hasanul Huq Inu, chairman of the Central Executive Committee of the Bangladesh National Socialist Party, in his statement on June 17 said that the Workers' Party of Korea has steadfastly carried forward the glorious history and the traditions of the Korean revolution while pulling through all the trials of history under Kim Jong Il's 40 odd year-long tested guidance and has wisely led the army and people to the final victory of socialism by foiling the imperialists' offensive to stifle the DPRK with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dilip Barua, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist), in a statement on the same day said that thanks to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK has demonstrated its might as an organizer and guide of all victories of the Korean people and commanded the positive support of the world revolutionary people for its great contribution to the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Siham Ahmad Mugahed, chairman of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association, in a statement on June 10 noted that the political philosophy of Kim Jong Il leading the revolution and construction to victory with his unique political mode is the Juche philosophy and it is the Songun politics that occupies the important place in his political mode. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saber Ballul, department head of the Political Faculty of the University of Damascus of Syria, in his statement on June 16 said that the WPK achieved its firm unity and cohesion under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and thus became able to advance straightly along the road of carrying out the cause of socialism without the slightest vacillation and twists and turns at a time when the communist and workers parties of the socialist countries in Eastern Europe were undergoing the tragedy of division and collapse.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Start of Work at C.C., WPK Observed in Bangladesh
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- The Bangladesh-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Committee issued a special bulletin on June 15 on the occasion of the 44th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin edited an article titled "Leader attaching importance to idea" and other articles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It in an article titled "Leader enjoying undisputed trust from people" stressed that Kim Jong Il is the outstanding leader possessed of the distinguished political caliber and noble trait. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that Kim Jong Il possessed of the extraordinary ideological and theoretical wisdom systematized the revolutionary idea, the Juche idea of President Kim Il Sung in an integral manner through his energetic ideological and theoretical activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has converted socialist Korea centered on the popular masses into a military power which the imperialist allied forces dare not to provoke by enforcing his original Songun politics, it said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has achieved the single-minded unity of the whole party and army and all the people with his outstanding organizing ability and led the revolution and construction to victory by motivating the people's thoughts, thus bringing about miracles and innovations in all fields including politics, military affairs, economy and culture.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Start of Work at C.C., WPK Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 24 (KCNA) -- Korean film shows took place in Germany and Indonesia from June 14 to 17 to mark the 44th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made by various figures at the shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of a cooperation organization of Germany praised Kim Jong Il as a great master of politics as he has developed the WPK into an invincible party guided by the Juche idea, noting that he published many works through his outstanding ideological and theoretical activities, thus clearly indicating the road to be followed by progressive humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager of a German company noted that the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration represents ardent patriotism of Kim Jong Il who conducted energetic activities to carry out the last instructions of President Kim Il Sung for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager and the deputy manager of the Rabitra Bahtera Pratama Co. of Indonesia stressed that the people of the DPRK would reap good fruits in building a great prosperous powerful nation and accomplishing the cause of national reunification thanks to the unique Songun politics.

Conversaciones entre delegaciones parlamentarias de Corea y Vietnam
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 24 de junio (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar este martes en el Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae las conversaciones entre la delegacion del grupo parlamentario de amistad Corea-Vietnam y la del grupo homologo Vietnam-Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
En la ocasion participaron por la parte coreana los miembros de la delegacion del grupo mencionado encabezada por su presidente Kim Wan Su y, por la vietnamita, los integrantes de la delegacion del grupo homologo dirigida por su presidente y titular del Consejo Nacional de la Asamblea Nacional de la Republica Socialista de Vietnam, Ksor Phuoc, y el embajador vietnamita en Corea Le Van Cu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ambas partes intercambiaron opiniones sobre el problema de desarrollar mas las relaciones de amistad y cooperacion entre los dos organos legislativos y otros asuntos de interes mutuo.

Acto por el 35o aniversario de obra de Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 24 de junio (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar el dia 23 en la Casa Central de la Juventud el acto de los capitalinos en homenaje al 35o aniversario de la publicacion de la obra del Presidente Kim Il Sung "Evitemos la division de la nacion y reunifiquemos la patria".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al conclave asistieron Kim Ki Nam, secretario del CC del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Kim Yong Dae, presidente del CC del Partido Social-Democrata de Corea, Ryu Mi Yong, presidenta del CC del Partido Chondoista Chong-U, Kang Ryon Hak, presidente del CC del Frente Democratico para la Reunificacion de la Patria, An Kyong Ho, director del Secretariado del Comite por la Reunificacion Pacifica de la Patria, y otros funcionarios directivos de las entidades sociales, asi como trabajadores capitalinos de distintos sectores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El informe de la ocasion estuvo a cargo de Kim Ki Nam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
La orientacion de 5 puntos para la reunificacion de la patria aclarada en la obra por el Presidente Kim Il Sung es autoctono programa de reunificacion y grandiosa plataforma politica por la unidad nacional que presento los remedios practicos para lograr la reunificacion rechazando la intervencion de las fuerzas foraneas y fomentando la reconciliacion entre el Norte y el Sur de Corea y la gran unidad pannacional mediante la materializacion global de la demanda de los tres principios de la reunificacion de la patria, comenzo el orador y continuo: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Gracias a la proclamacion de esa orientacion, la nacion coreana pudo librar con mas vigor la lucha por cumplir esa causa nacional guiandose por la hoja de ruta mas justa y realista. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La causa de reunificacion de la patria iniciada y orientada por el Presidente la lleva adelante con exito el Dirigente Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mediante sus entusiastas actividades ideo-teoricas, el Dirigente sistematizo integralmente la idea y las proezas de direccion del Presidente sobre la reunificacion de la patria e ilumino el rumbo del movimiento para el particular. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
De esta manera, fue abierta la nueva coyuntura trascendental en la lucha por la reunificacion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta causa es el legado del Presidente y la suprema tarea nacional para los coreanos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Debemos atenernos firmemente a la linea y la orientacion originales del PTC en materia de reunificacion y materializarlas cabalmente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Debido a las maniobras del circulo militar norteamericano y los belicistas surcoreanos para desatar la guerra de agresion contra la RPDC, se exacerba cada dia mas la tension de la Peninsula Coreana y se agranda de dia en dia el peligro de guerra nuclear. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Esta realidad demuestra claramente que es invariable la naturaleza agresiva de EE.UU. y el "poder" belicoso del Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Todos los partidos politicos, entidades y distintos sectores del Norte, el Sur y ultramar deben hacer contribuciones especiales a la reunificacion de la patria y a la coprosperidad nacional anteponiendo los intereses nacionales a las ideas, regimenes, criterios politicos, creencias religiosas e intereses fraccionalistas y dinamizar el movimiento pannacional por la reunificacion fortaleciendo la solidaridad y la alianza.
